1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
This is Al Brooks and this is module 4 of my price action trading course and today I'm going to talk about the personality traits of successful traders.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Everyone's familiar with the list of traits that are many more than this. Some are fairly obvious. Being objective, being disciplined, being patient.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:30,000
The two last ones I think are probably the most important. Being comfortable with uncertainty and managing trades properly.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Discipline traders, they never say to themselves, maybe this time it'll work. I'll try it this time. Or hey, maybe I'll try this.

5
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:50,000
They don't try ideas out of the blue whimsically just because the market is setting up something that might be fun to try.

6
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:59,000
They stick to their plan and if a setup is not one that they normally trade or if it's something that doesn't look quite right, they just don't take the trade.

7
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:09,000
They just let it go. Discipline traders, they never say to themselves, maybe this time it'll work. I'll try it this time. Or hey, maybe I'll try this.

8
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:19,000
They don't try ideas out of the blue whimsically just because the market is setting up something that might be fun to try.

9
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:28,000
They stick to their plan and if a setup is not one that they normally trade or if it's something that doesn't look quite right, they just don't take the trade.

10
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
They just let it go.

11
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:37,000
And you're trading against computers and you're trying to duplicate what they're doing.

12
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Institutions are mostly computer generated trades and if you're to make money, you've got to be doing what the institutions are doing and what the computers are doing and they're not trading based on emotion.

13
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:59,000
So if you're looking at a setup and you feel any emotion, don't take the trade.

14
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:09,000
You also have to be very comfortable with the idea that the market might do the exact opposite of what you believe and it'll happen about 40% of the time.

15
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,000
It can happen more.

16
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:15,000
If you're a scalper and you're extremely good, it can happen less.

17
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:21,000
But you have to be open to the possibility that the market can do the exact opposite of what you think.

18
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Remember that any time you take a trade, an institution agrees with you and another institution disagrees with you and you cannot be so confident that the institution on the other side is wrong.

19
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:45,000
That institution, no matter how confident you are, is going to be right 40% of the time, at least 40% of the time.

20
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:51,000
So if you're a pretty good trader, you'll probably lose at least 40% of the time.

21
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:55,000
You have to be willing to sit there and do nothing.

22
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:09,000
If you're a day trader, sometimes you have to sit for an hour or two or three waiting for a good signal and never get impatient and start telling yourself that, boy, a good trade is overdue.

23
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Maybe I'll take this one.

24
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,000
A good trade is never overdue.

25
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Sometimes there'll be 20 or 30 good signals in a day, sometimes just three or four.

26
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:26,000
And if you want to end up positive at the end of the day, you'll just accept whatever the market is offering.

27
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:35,000
And if it's offering very little, then you have to sit there patiently and do nothing.

28
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,000
This is very important, the idea of being comfortable with uncertainty.

29
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Whenever you're putting on a trade, there's always uncertainty.

30
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:51,000
The first obvious element of uncertainty is how likely will the trade be successful?

31
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:55,000
What's the probability of success of achieving your goals?

32
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:59,000
And then you're also going to be uncertain about where to put the stop.

33
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Do you use your routine stop, money stop, like maybe two points in the E-mini, maybe 50 cents in IBM?

34
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Or do you have to use a bigger stop or a smaller stop?

35
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,000
You're also going to be uncertain about your profit target.

36
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:24,000
If the bars are very big and the range is very big and the swings are very big, maybe you should be using larger targets.

37
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:28,000
And this is something that traders deal with all the time.

38
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:38,000
If you find yourself getting upset or anxious or feeling pressured that you don't have enough time to make the decision, don't take the trade.

39
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Because then you're feeling emotion and you cannot make money if emotion is influencing your decisions because you're trying to do what the computers are doing

40
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,000
and they are not trading based on emotion.

41
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:58,000
You have to be comfortable with losses. They're going to come.

42
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:02,000
If you're a pretty good trader, you're going to be losing at least 40% of the time.

43
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:07,000
When you're trading, nothing is crystal clear as you're trading.

44
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:13,000
And if you think something is crystal clear, don't take the trade because you're reading the charts incorrectly.

45
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:17,000
At the end of the day, when you print out the chart, everything is crystal clear.

46
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:23,000
However, that's not the case real time. There's always uncertainty.

47
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
You also have to be comfortable with what you're doing.

48
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:33,000
If this is your job and you're planning on doing it for many years, you have to be doing it in a way that's enjoyable.

49
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:41,000
You can't be miserably stressed out all day long, worried about losing money and worried that, oh my gosh, I just lost three in a row.

50
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
I can't afford losing four in a row.

51
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:49,000
If that's how you're feeling, you have to change how you're trading

52
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:55,000
and find a method to trade where you enjoy what you're doing.

53
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:59,000
I get up every morning and I just can't wait to get in front of my computer.

54
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,000
I really like what I'm doing.

55
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:08,000
For years, I was an extreme scalper taking 40 trades a day, but it was really stressful.

56
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,000
It was not fun. Can you make more money doing that?

57
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Sure, but life has to be fun. You only have so many years and if you're choosing to live them in a miserable way,

58
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:25,000
I think that's not the best way to live your life.

59
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:32,000
I think what you do with your life time is precious and every part of your life should be fun.

60
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:38,000
You can make money while being happy.

61
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:43,000
There are lots of jobs where you can really love what you're doing and you can make a lot of money.

62
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Trading is one of them. You don't have to be miserably worried all the time.

63
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:55,000
You have to find a way of trading that allows you to be happy.

64
00:06:55,000 --> 00:07:03,000
There are lots of ways to trade and chances are you'll be able to find one that suits your personality.

65
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Don't worry if you see someone on television who's trading one way and it's not right for you.

66
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:18,000
That's okay. Every trader has a different personality and every trader finds a method of trading that suits their personality.

67
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:24,000
The great traders don't worry that somebody else is using some other approach and making a lot of money.

68
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:31,000
If that's not them, then don't worry about it. You have to be comfortable doing what you have to do.

69
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Swing traders lose most of the time but they're going for rewards that are two or three times greater than their risk.

70
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:47,000
If they're comfortable with winning only 40% of the time, it's a great way to trade.

71
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:51,000
In fact, it's probably the best way to trade when a trader is starting out.

72
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Other traders are comfortable scaling into trades and going against them.

73
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:05,000
For example, if the market is in a weak bull channel, they'll start selling above prior swing highs.

74
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:10,000
If they're confident that the channel is about to transform into a trading range or reversal.

75
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:14,000
But they have to be comfortable with growing open losses.

76
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:19,000
The losses that they have continue to grow as the channel continues to go up.

77
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,000
They also have to be confident in their read.

78
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:28,000
They have to be confident that the channel is trying to convert into a trading range.

79
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:32,000
They also have to be able to stick to their plan.

80
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:40,000
They can't panic and exit with a huge loss right before the market turns.

81
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:48,000
They have to be trading with a size that will allow them to have the market go against them sometimes for an hour or two.

82
00:08:48,000 --> 00:09:01,000
But as long as they're confident with their read and they're not trading so large that the losses are too big for what they're doing.

83
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,000
That's a comfortable way to trade.

84
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:10,000
There are other traders, scalpers, who want a very high probability trade.

85
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:17,000
But anytime something has a high probability of working, chances are it's only going to work briefly.

86
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:20,000
So the reward is going to be smaller.

87
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:32,000
However, even if you're scalping for a small reward, you have to make sure that your risk, the distance to your stop, is no bigger than your reward.

88
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:39,000
If you're trading with a stop that's bigger than your profit target, you have to be right 80 or 90% of the time.

89
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:44,000
And that's very difficult to do.

90
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Some traders are comfortable with any type of environment.

91
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:53,000
High probability, low probability, scalps and swings.

92
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,000
And that's okay.

93
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:58,000
And if you find yourself to be one of those traders, go for it.

94
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
If that's your comfort zone, that's fine.

95
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
Go for it.

96
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Managing trades correctly is, I think, the most important part of trading.

97
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,000
And it's more important than spotting perfect setups.

98
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,000
You know, it's fairly easy to spot setups.

99
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
It's fairly easy to spot really good setups.

100
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:21,000
But it can be difficult to manage the trade correctly after you put the trade on.

101
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Most of the time, there's a profitable way to manage both a long and a short.

102
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:32,000
So most of the time, at any given instant during the day, you could buy and make money.

103
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:35,000
You can sell and make money if you manage your trades correctly.

104
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,000
How can that be?

105
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Well, let's say you buy.

106
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:43,000
There's an institution taking the other side of that trade and chances are they're profitable.

107
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:48,000
So they have a profitable way to make money selling to you.

108
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:53,000
But that's management and you have to be able to do it well.

109
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:58,000
So anyway, like I just said, at any given instant, a good trader usually can make money

110
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:04,000
by either buying or selling if they manage their trades correctly.

111
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,000
This is the end of Module 4.

112
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,000
Thank you.
